'title': 'substring similar - extra characters in the result for non latin characters',
'description':
 """
    Confirmed regression on build 4.0.0.1629, 4.0.0.1631 
	Worked as expected on 4.0.0.1535 (build 24.06.2019, before replacement old regexp library with 're2')
    Works fine on: 4.0.0.1632 (build 19.10.2019)

    28.02.2021
    Regression on 4.0.0.1629 can be reproduced only when connection charset is WIN1251. NO problem with UTF8.
    Becase of this, attribute 'platform' was restricted to be run only on Windows.
    On Linux this test (with use connection_character_set = 'WIN1251') leads to compilation error:
    ====
      Statement failed, SQLSTATE = 42000
      Dynamic SQL Error
      -SQL error code = -104
      -Token unknown - line 4, column 1
      -ommit
    ====
 """,
'min_versions': '4.0',
